X JAPAN的音樂植根於英美的[[重金屬音樂|重金屬音樂]]、[[華麗金屬|華麗金屬]]、[[鞭擊金屬|鞭擊金屬]]與[[朋克搖滾|龐克搖滾]]，他們受到[[接吻樂團|接吻樂團]]、[[深紫|深紫]]、[[齐柏林飞船_(乐团)|齊柏林飛船]]、[[猶大祭司|猶大祭司]]、[[鐵娘子樂團|鐵娘子]]、[[摩托頭|摩托頭]]、{{link-en|彩虹 (英國樂團)|Rainbow (rock band)|彩虹}}、[[皇后樂團|皇后樂團]]、[[披頭四樂團|披頭四樂團]]以及{{link-en|幽浮 (樂團)|UFO (band)|幽浮}}的影響<ref name="rock7356925">{{Cite web|language=en|author=Natasha Scharf|title=Who the hell are X Japan?|url=http://teamrock.com/feature/2014-08-13/who-the-hell-are-x-japan|publisher=TeamRock|date=2014-08-13|accessdate=2017-02-25|archive-date=2017-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170225205605/http://teamrock.com/feature/2014-08-13/who-the-hell-are-x-japan|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="JaME World">{{Cite web|language=en|url=http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-78572-taiji-sawada-memorial.html|title=Taiji Sawada Memorial|date=2011-09-04|accessdate=2016-08-16|publisher=JaME World|archive-date=2016-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331192425/http://jame-world.com/us/articles-78572-taiji-sawada-memorial.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。樂團的音樂特色是[[速度金屬|速度金屬]]、[[力量金屬|力量金屬]]和[[交響金屬|交響金屬]]（如〈紅〉、〈SILENT JEALOUSY〉），以及[[軟式搖滾|抒情搖滾]]（如〈[[ENDLESS_RAIN|ENDLESS RAIN]]〉、〈FOREVER LOVE〉）<ref name="NYTimes">{{cite news| language = en| last = Strauss| first = Neil| title = The Pop Life: End of a Life, End of an Era| work = [[紐約時報|紐約時報]]| date = 1998-06-18| url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9D00EFD7103DF93BA25755C0A96E958260&sec=&spon=&pagewanted=all| accessdate = 2007-08-06| archive-date = 2009-03-10| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090310160920/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9D00EFD7103DF93BA25755C0A96E958260&sec=&spon=&pagewanted=all| dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name="asiaarts_x_best">{{cite web |language=en |last=Minnie |first=Chi |title=''X Japan Best'' review |work=Asia Pacific Arts Online Magazine |url=http://www.asiaarts.ucla.edu/article.asp?parentid=7936 |accessdate=2007-09-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071011140930/http://asiaarts.ucla.edu/article.asp?parentid=7936 |archivedate=2007-10-11 }}</ref><ref name="amg_bio">{{cite web|language = en| last = Seida| first = Linda| title = X Japan biography at Allmusic| work = [[Allmusic|Allmusic]]| url = {{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p320432|pure_url=yes}}| accessdate = 2007-08-06}}</ref>。樂團的許多歌曲都運用到[[管弦樂團|管弦樂團]]，尤其是在時間較長的歌曲，如十分鐘的〈TEARS〉、〈CRUCIFY MY LOVE〉，以及二十九分鐘的〈ART OF LIFE〉。大多數歌曲以樂團的母語（[[日語|日語]]）填詞，但許多情況下顯示，有些歌曲是參雜著日語和[[英語|英語]]，如〈RUSTY NAIL〉中間的獨白和聲，以及〈WEEK END〉中都是。首張專輯《VANISHING VISION》中收錄的〈紅〉初版完全是英語歌詞。

X JAPAN的歌曲大部分是由YOSHIKI譜寫創作，其他成員的比重相對較少。Hide貢獻了幾首歌曲，如〈[[Scars|SCARS]]〉。而PATA則是〈White Wind from Mr. Martin ~Pata's Nap~〉。TOSHI的創作僅限於幾首歌的歌詞。TAIJI為一些歌曲貢獻了作曲，特別是專輯《Jealousy》中收錄的〈VOICELESS SCREAMING〉，並由他負責[[原聲吉他|原聲吉他]]彈奏的部分。HEATH則在1996年專輯《DAHLIA》中與PATA共同創作了〈WRIGGLE〉。只有一首歌是五位成員共同創作的：〈EASY FIGHT RAMBLING〉，該曲收錄在1989年專輯《BLUE BLOOD》。一位較無知名度的地下時期成員JUN貢獻了〈TIME TRIP LOVING〉的作曲。據2010年日媒報導，SUGIZO已經寫了一些歌曲，但沒有進一步消息釋出<ref>{{cite web |language=en |title=X JAPAN Heading Towards Their First American Tour in October. YOSHIKI "This is a restart in various meanings." |url=http://www.musicjapanplus.jp/news/1/5024/x-japan-heading-towards-their-first-american-tour-in-october-yoshiki-this-is-a-restart-in-various-meanings/ |work=[[Musicjapanplus|Musicjapanplus]] |date=2010-07-09 |accessdate=2012-06-03 |archive-date=2012-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120303053828/http://www.musicjapanplus.jp/news/1/5024/x%2Djapan%2Dheading%2Dtowards%2Dtheir%2Dfirst%2Damerican%2Dtour%2Din%2Doctober%2Dyoshiki%2Dthis%2Dis%2Da%2Drestart%2Din%2Dvarious%2Dmeanings/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。同年，YOSHIKI表示他們的新創作「幾乎是一樣的東西，也許會比較激情一點點」<ref>{{cite web |language=en |title=EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW WITH X JAPAN’S YOSHIKI HAYASHI |url=http://www.metalsucks.net/2010/10/08/exclusive-interview-with-x-japans-yoshiki-hayashi/ |work={{link-en|MetalSucks|MetalSucks}} date=2010-10-08 |accessdate=2014-05-23 |archive-date=2014-03-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140314103123/http://www.metalsucks.net/2010/10/08/exclusive-interview-with-x-japans-yoshiki-hayashi/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。然而在2014年，他特別指出，新的作品將和以往不同，並補充說：「聲音將會非常重、更旋律性、也更現代化」<ref>{{cite web |language=en |title=Metal Legend Yoshiki of X Japan Gets His Ovation at the Grammys |url=http://www.mtviggy.com/articles/metal-legend-yoshiki-of-x-japan-gets-his-ovation-at-the-grammys/ |work=[[MTV|MTV]] |accessdate=2014-05-23 |archive-date=2014-05-23 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20140523045425/http://www.mtviggy.com/articles/metal-legend-yoshiki-of-x-japan-gets-his-ovation-at-the-grammys/ |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

YOSHIKI的詞曲創作過程較不尋常，他在2016年表示[[音樂記譜法|樂譜]]會先於一切完成，然後樂團才開始演奏排練，包括吉他和鼓，之後如有必要再進行修改潤飾<ref name="drums">{{cite web| language=en| url=http://www.musicradar.com/news/drums/yoshiki-x-japan-10-drummers-that-blew-my-mind-631353| title=Yoshiki, X Japan: 10 drummers that blew my mind| publisher={{link-en|MusicRadar|MusicRadar}}| date=2015-11-30| accessdate=2016-01-30| archive-date=2016-03-06| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306030931/http://www.musicradar.com/news/drums/yoshiki-x-japan-10-drummers-that-blew-my-mind-631353| dead-url=yes}}</ref>。他的創作風格趨向於運用前後相鄰八度的[[和弦|和弦]]，或者跨度更大的和弦，以及使用呼應手法的編曲方式。他的職業生涯中大部分是擔任[[作曲家|作曲家]]，從四歲就開始學習彈奏[[鋼琴|鋼琴]]，他稱自己的[[搖滾樂|搖滾樂]]風格受到[[古典音樂|古典音樂]]的影響，而他在擔任[[音樂製作人|音樂製作人]]的成果上，在音樂界具有十足的信譽。現場表演時，樂團大部分會有成員切換樂器來演奏，如YOSHIKI會在爵士鼓和鋼琴間交換，SUGIZO會在吉他與[[小提琴|小提琴]]間交換。並且也會播放預錄的[[弦樂|弦樂]]、{{link-en|獨白和聲|Spoken word}}，以及一些hide生前錄下的歌聲和吉他音源<ref name="wowow_live_2008-03-28">{{Cite journal| title = Live broadcast of the 28 March 2008 Tokyo Dome concert| work = [[WOWOW|WOWOW]]| date = 2008-03-28}}</ref>。

==視覺外型==
{{Cquote 3|當我們演奏很重、很激烈的音樂時，我反其道而行，加入一些女性化的特徵。當我們演奏抒情歌時，我卻是頂著高聳的怒髮。|author=[[YOSHIKI|YOSHIKI]] |source=英國《{{link-en|Dazed|Dazed}}》雜誌<ref name="dazed">{{cite web|url=http://www.dazeddigital.com/music/article/34948/1/x-japan-we-are-x-speed-metal-band-david-lynch|title=Sects, suicide & speed metal: the unreal story of X Japan|publisher={{link-en|Dazed|Dazed}}|accessdate=2017-04-18|date=2017-03-01|archive-date=2017-04-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170419003025/http://www.dazeddigital.com/music/article/34948/1/x-japan-we-are-x-speed-metal-band-david-lynch|dead-url=yes}}</ref>}}
X JAPAN的外型裝扮受到[[華麗搖滾|華麗搖滾]]影響，例如[[接吻樂團|接吻樂團]]、[[大衛·鮑伊|大衛·鮑伊]]，以及日本[[歌舞伎|歌舞伎]]劇場的傳統藝術啟發，以男性身份去扮演女性角色，甚至穿上女裝。因他們而開啟的[[視覺系|視覺系]]風格中，該類型的音樂人至今仍然經常採用女性化的外觀和舞台服裝<ref name="dazed" /><ref name="Yun2">{{cite book|author=Josephine Yun|title=Jrock, Ink.: A Concise Report on 40 of the Biggest Rock Acts in Japan |url=https://archive.org/details/jrockinkconciser0000yunj|chapter=Introduction|page=[https://archive.org/details/jrockinkconciser0000yunj/page/11 11]|publisher=Stone Bridge Press|isbn=9781880656952 |year=2005}}</ref><ref name="Yun">{{cite book|author=Josephine Yun|title=Jrock, Ink.: A Concise Report on 40 of the Biggest Rock Acts in Japan |url=https://archive.org/details/jrockinkconciser0000yunj|chapter=X Japan|page=[https://archive.org/details/jrockinkconciser0000yunj/page/110 110]|publisher=Stone Bridge Press|isbn=9781880656952 |year=2005}}</ref><ref name="GlobalGlam">{{cite book|title=Global Glam and Popular Music: Style and Spectacle from the 1970s to the 2000s|pages=203–205|publisher=Routledge|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RY-PCwAAQBAJ&pg=PA204&lpg=PA204&dq=X+Japan+androgynous+look&source=bl&ots=K51S9lkj6u&sig=V-E090uqEbuXNrMiNWeQscUBZXA&hl=hu&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjaufi6iOPTAhXJLlAKHaKLDUMQ6AEIQTAI#v=onepage&q=X%20Japan%20androgynous%20look&f=false|editor= Ian Chapman, Henry Johnson|year=2016|isbn=9781317588191}}</ref>。作家{{link-en|約瑟芬·尹|Josephine Yun}}介紹說：「就像它的音樂一樣，X JAPAN的外型充滿了[[個人主義|個人主義]]，TOSHI穿上肩線十分方正的金屬皮衣，看起來就像[[動畫|動畫]]《[[鋼彈系列作品|鋼彈]]》中的角色一樣，TAIJI的打扮既完美又華麗，PATA頹廢慵懶、低調的風格和威士忌酒瓶成為他的個人特色，而HIDE永遠吸引著觀眾目光。至於YOSHIKI整個人就像是一種[[悖論|悖論]]，能在傾刻之間令人瞠目結舌——以及在舞台上那種壯士斷腕般的暴風面向」<ref name="Yun" />。《[[泰晤士報|泰晤士報]]》記者{{link-en|威爾·霍奇金森|Will Hodgkinson}}描述X JAPAN具有「[[皇后樂團|皇后樂團]]般的宏大威儀，[[鐵娘子樂團|鐵娘子]]歇斯底里的[[重金屬音樂|重金屬音樂]]和複雜的[[古典音樂|古典音樂]]，所有元素都像一部音樂劇完美的綁在一起」<ref name="The Times">{{Cite news|last=Hodgkinson|first=Will|authorlink=Will Hodgkinson|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/the-worlds-unluckiest-band-the-bizarre-story-ofxjapan-x9lwclhbx|title=The world's unluckiest band: the bizarre story of X Japan|newspaper=[[泰晤士報|泰晤士報]]|date=2017-10-13|accessdate=2017-10-14|archive-date=2017-10-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171014134430/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/the-worlds-unluckiest-band-the-bizarre-story-ofxjapan-x9lwclhbx|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

他們早期外型特點是化很濃的妝、深色眼線和眼影、臉部彩繪和高聳的髮型，評論家形容為「摩天大樓般的頭髮」。YOSHIKI的樣子極具[[雙性性格|雙性性格]]，身上穿戴著[[蕾絲|蕾絲]]和珍珠。樂團成員使用的裝飾讓人想起[[哥德次文化|華麗哥德]]（金屬飾品、十字）。他們的舞台體現了自然界的雙重性質：陽剛且男性化的重金屬歌曲、TOSHI高亢平衡的[[男高音|男高音]]歌聲，和YOSHIKI優雅的鋼琴演奏，舞台上的他經常會穿連身的女性身裙，並展現陰柔脆弱的姿態<ref name="GlobalGlam"/>。

1995年，樂團發行第五張錄音室專輯《{{link-ja|DAHLIA|DAHLIA (アルバム)}}》之際，他們改變了表演造型、剪短頭髮、改穿更具搖滾風格的服裝<ref name="GlobalGlam"/>。YOSHIKI在2010年的採訪中指出，拋棄強烈的妝容和極度華麗的服裝，其實是他們風格上的自然發展，但至今站上舞台時仍會化淡妝，「有時濃一點，有時淡一點」，他仍然認為X JAPAN是一支視覺系樂團<ref name="Metalsucks">{{cite web|url=http://www.metalsucks.net/2010/10/08/exclusive-interview-with-x-japans-yoshiki-hayashi/|title=EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW WITH X JAPAN’S YOSHIKI HAYASHI|date=2010-10-08|accessdate=2017-04-18|publisher=MetalSucks|archive-date=2017-08-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170816052811/http://www.metalsucks.net/2010/10/08/exclusive-interview-with-x-japans-yoshiki-hayashi/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==影響力、開創性、成就與地位==
美國[[MTV|MTV]]電視台形容X JAPAN是「日本歷史上最具影響力的樂團」、「文化／音樂／時尚運動的領導者之一」<ref name="MTVBIO">{{Cite web|language=en|title=X Japan's Yoshiki On Pain, Loss, Prince and the Band's First Album in 20 Years|url=http://www.mtv.com/artists/x-japan/|publisher=[[MTV|MTV]]|accessdate=2017-02-25|archive-date=2017-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170226052655/http://www.mtv.com/artists/x-japan/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。美國《[[告示牌_(雜誌)|告示牌]]》雜誌表示，X JAPAN在90年代中期便贏得「日本有史以來最大的樂團」的地位，也是公認的[[視覺系|視覺系]]創始者<ref>{{Cite web|language=en|author=Dan Rys|title=X Japan's Yoshiki On Pain, Loss, Prince and the Band's First Album in 20 Years|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/7356925/x-japan-yoshiki-pain-loss-prince-first-album-20-years|publisher=[[告示牌_(雜誌)|告示牌]]|date=2016-05-06|accessdate=2017-02-25|archive-date=2017-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170226135544/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/7356925/x-japan-yoshiki-pain-loss-prince-first-album-20-years|dead-url=no}}</ref>，他們在日本掀起巨大的音樂運動，類似於西方國家的[[華麗搖滾|華麗搖滾]]風潮，視覺系的命名來自於樂團最初的團名「X - Psychedelic Violence: Crime of Visual Shock（X ─ 迷幻狂暴：視覺衝擊之罪）」<ref name="NYTimes"/><ref name="bounce">{{cite web| last = Dejima| first = Kouji| title = Bounce Di(s)ctionary Number 13 – Visual Kei| work = bounce.com| language = ja| url = http://www.bounce.com/article/article.php/3419/| accessdate = 2013-08-10| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080301175244/http://www.bounce.com/article/article.php/3419/| archivedate = 2008-03-01| dead-url = yes}}</ref>。2011年，YOSHIKI簡要描述了他們早期發起的音樂運動：
{{Cquote 3|當時我們組了團，卻不受任何地方接納，因為我們的音樂很重，穿著非常瘋狂的服裝、臉上也化誇張的妝，所以完全沒有地方容得下我們。但我們堅持做自己想做的，最終成為視覺系。但是視覺系更像是一種精神，它不是一種音樂風格，或者... 你懂的... 我認為這是一種坦率表達自己，擁有自由意識的一種『自由』，我相信視覺系就是主張這樣的精神<ref name="visualkei">{{Cite web|language=en|title=Interview with YOSHIKI in Brazil|url=http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-80940-interview-with-yoshiki-in-brazil.html|publisher={{link-es|JaME|JaME}}|date=2011-11-20|accessdate=2013-03-08|archive-date=2013-05-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130509054400/http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-80940-interview-with-yoshiki-in-brazil.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。}}

1998年，在樂團解散還不到一年時，吉他手hide意外身亡，美國《[[告示牌_(雜誌)|告示牌]]》雜誌的東京分部負責人{{link-en|史蒂夫·麥克魯 (記者)|Steve McClure (reporter)|史蒂夫·麥克魯}}宣布：「一個生命的結束，也代表一個時代的結束。X JAPAN是視覺系的始祖，對於下一代的樂團來說，這也代表[[火炬|火炬]]已經傳到你們的手上了」<ref name="NYTimes"/>。

許多樂團和-{音樂人}-（通常是視覺系）都曾表示，受到X JAPAN的影響甚鉅，也非常崇仰他們。例如[[雅-miyavi-|雅-miyavi-]]<ref name="Miyavi">{{Cite web|language=en|title=Exclusive interview with miyavi|url=http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-1054-exclusive-interview-with-miyavi.html|work=jame-world.com|date=2006-09-17|accessdate=2013-03-02|archive-date=2013-05-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130509032334/http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-1054-exclusive-interview-with-miyavi.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>、[[Galneryus|Galneryus]]的成員[[Syu|Syu]]<ref name="Syu">{{Cite web|language=en|title=Exclusive interview with Syu|url=http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-1503-exclusive-interview-with-syu.html|work=jame-world.com|date=2006-12-15|accessdate=2013-03-02|archive-date=2013-05-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130509050524/http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-1503-exclusive-interview-with-syu.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>、[[the_GazettE|the GazettE]]<ref name="Gazette">{{Cite web|language=en|title=The GazettE Interview|url=http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-85-the-gazette-interview.html|work=jame-world.com|date=2006-08-04|accessdate=2013-03-02|archive-date=2013-05-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130509050833/http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-85-the-gazette-interview.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>、{{link-en|Sadie|Sadie (band)}}的成員Mao<ref name="Mao">{{Cite web|language=en|title=VISUAL JAPAN SUMMIT 2016 Day 2: Part 1|url=http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-123274-visual-japan-summit-2016-day-2-part-1.html|work=jame-world.com|accessdate=2016-11-16|archive-date=2016-11-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117064710/http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-123274-visual-japan-summit-2016-day-2-part-1.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>、[[12012|12012]]的成員川內　亨<ref name="Toru">{{cite web|language=en|title=12012 in 2010|url=http://jrockrevolution.com/2011/03/webzine/12012-in-2010-306|work=JRock Revolution|date=2011-04-18|accessdate=2013-03-02|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141011233310/http://jrockrevolution.com/2011/03/webzine/12012-in-2010-306|archivedate=2014-10-11|dead-url=yes}}</ref>、[[LM.C|LM.C]]的成員{{link-en|Maya (音樂人)|Maya (musician)|Maya}}<ref name="Maya">{{Cite web|language=en|title=An Interview with LM.C in France|url=http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-48576-an-interview-with-lm-c-in-france.html|work=jame-world.com|date=2009-06-02|accessdate=2013-03-02|archive-date=2013-05-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130509061408/http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-48576-an-interview-with-lm-c-in-france.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>、[[FLOW_(樂團)|Flow]]<ref name="Flow">{{cite web|language=en|title=live report + interview Power FLOWing Through Music at Anime Matsuri|url=http://purpleskymagazine.com/2012/04/live-report-interview-power-flowing-through-music-at-anime-matsuri/|work=Purple Sky Magazine|date=2012-04-16|accessdate=2014-12-12|archive-date=2014-12-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141213013723/http://purpleskymagazine.com/2012/04/live-report-interview-power-flowing-through-music-at-anime-matsuri/|dead-url=yes}}</ref>、{{link-en|Unsraw|Unsraw}}的成員Yuuki<ref name="Yuuki">{{Cite web|language=en|title=Morning Meeting with UnsraW|url=http://www.jame-world.com/uk/articles-61884-morning-meeting-with-unsraw.html|work=jame-world.com|date=2010-06-03|accessdate=2013-03-02|archive-date=2013-05-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130509031613/http://www.jame-world.com/uk/articles-61884-morning-meeting-with-unsraw.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>、{{link-en|DJ Ozma|DJ Ozma}}<ref name="Ozma & Luna Sea">{{cite web|language=en|title=hide Memorial Summit Press Conference|url=http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-4545-hide-memorial-summit-press-conference.html|work=jame-world.com|accessdate=2013-08-30|archive-date=2013-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130605212733/http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-4545-hide-memorial-summit-press-conference.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>、{{link-en|Dio – Distraught Overlord|Dio – Distraught Overlord}}的成員Kei<ref name="Kei">{{cite web|language=en|title=DIO ~Distraught Overlord~ Press Conference|url=http://jrockrevolution.com/2008/12/webzine/dio-distraught-overlord-press-conference-257|work=JRock Revolution|date=2008-12-29|accessdate=2013-03-02|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141011233407/http://jrockrevolution.com/2008/12/webzine/dio-distraught-overlord-press-conference-257|archivedate=2014-10-11|dead-url=yes}}</ref>、{{link-en|Deadman|Deadman (band)}}的成員aie<ref name="aie">{{cite web|language=en|title=Biography Special: aie|url=http://www.jame-world.com/uk/articles-71208-biography-special-aie.html|work=jame-world.com|date=2011-01-07|accessdate=2013-03-02|archive-date=2013-05-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130509062525/http://www.jame-world.com/uk/articles-71208-biography-special-aie.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>、{{link-en|Screw|Screw (band)}}的成員Jin<ref name="Jin">{{cite web|language=en|title=Interview with SCREW during J-ROCK INVASION|url=http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-4086-interview-with-screw-during-j-rock-invasion.html|work=jame-world.com|date=2008-03-01|accessdate=2013-03-02|archive-date=2013-05-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130509064331/http://www.jame-world.com/us/articles-4086-interview-with-screw-during-j-rock-invasion.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>、[[DaizyStripper|DaizyStripper]]<ref name="DaizyStripper">{{cite web|language=en|title=Interview with DaizyStripper|url=http://jrockrevolution.com/2008/12/webzine/interview-with-daizystripper-252|work=JRock Revolution|date=2008-12-10|accessdate=2013-03-02|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208062715/http://jrockrevolution.com/2008/12/webzine/interview-with-daizystripper-252|archivedate=2015-12-08|dead-url=yes}}</ref>和[[五月天|五月天]]<ref name="wearexDocumentary"/>。[[Versailles_-Philharmonic_Quintet-|凡爾賽宮]]的成員表示受到X JAPAN和[[月之海|月之海]]的影響，主唱[[KAMIJO|KAMIJO]]說：「我認為日本音樂界中，沒有任何人不受他們影響」<ref>{{cite web|language=en|title=Descendants of Roses: Versailles Interview Part 2|url=http://jrockrevolution.com/2008/03/webzine/descendants-of-roses-versailles-interview-part-2-227|work=JRock Revolution|date=2008-03-06|accessdate=2013-03-02|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141107165558/http://jrockrevolution.com/2008/03/webzine/descendants-of-roses-versailles-interview-part-2-227|archivedate=2014-11-07|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。{{link-ja|LADIESROOM|LADIESROOM}}表示：「因為他們，搖滾在日本才能有一席之地」<ref name="wearexDocumentary"/>。月之海說：「他們對音樂的態度、激情，是我們的榜樣」<ref name="wearexDocumentary"/>。[[Dir_en_grey|Dir en grey]]則說：「YOSHIKI讓我們這些下一代敢於夢想，如果說有一座我們都渴望能翻越的高山，X JAPAN就是那座山」<ref name="wearexDocumentary"/><ref name="dir en grey">{{Cite web|language=en|title=X Japan Interview|url=http://www.jerseybeat.com/xjapan.html|work=jerseybeat.com|accessdate=2013-04-20|archive-date=2014-10-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141014200152/http://www.jerseybeat.com/xjapan.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="dir en grey 2">{{cite web| language = en| title = Shock-rock act Dir En Grey snub cartoons for cred| work = [[The_Japan_Times|The Japan Times]]| url = http://www.japantimes.co.jp/culture/2010/12/17/music/shock-rock-act-dir-en-grey-snub-cartoons-for-cred/#.UXxLj8pArIV| date = 2010-12-17| accessdate = 2013-04-27| archive-date = 2013-11-13| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20131113192102/http://www.japantimes.co.jp/culture/2010/12/17/music/shock-rock-act-dir-en-grey-snub-cartoons-for-cred/#.UXxLj8pArIV| dead-url = no}}</ref>。

同樣，Galneryus和{{link-en|Deluhi|Deluhi}}的吉他手[[Leda|Leda]]也說：「以前原本對音樂沒有特別興趣，直到有個朋友給我聽了X JAPAN和月之海。現在，X JAPAN的專輯已經是我的《[[聖經|聖經]]》了」<ref>{{cite web|language=en|title=Interview: DELUHI|url=http://jrockrevolution.com/2009/05/webzine/interview-deluhi-269|work=JRock Revolution|date=2009-05-14|accessdate=2013-03-02|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141011233510/http://jrockrevolution.com/2009/05/webzine/interview-deluhi-269|archivedate=2014-10-11|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。美國金屬音樂人、前[[麥加帝斯|麥加帝斯]]吉他手[[马蒂·弗里德曼_(音乐家)|馬蒂·弗里德曼]]稱X JAPAN是日本最偉大的視覺系樂團和「史上最多才多藝的音樂性」，並指出樂團是使他逐漸親近[[日本搖滾樂|日本搖滾樂]]的原因：「他們是日本最快最重的音樂，還有一絲抒情民謠搖滾的成分。他們的做法是對的，這讓我驚訝於『他們是怎麼辦到的』」<ref name="GlobalMetal">{{cite AV media |language = en|author1=Marty Friedman |author2= Yoshiki |date=2008-06-20 |title={{link-en|Global Metal|Global Metal}} |medium=Motion picture |publisher=}}</ref>。

樂評人有島博志表示：「他們的音樂特別快，他們的破壞力和侵略性是任何樂團都比不上的」<ref name="wearexDocumentary">{{cite AV media |language = en|author={{link-en|Stephen Kijak|Stephen Kijak}}|date=2016-10-21 |title=[[WE_ARE_X：X_JAPAN重生之路|WE ARE X：X JAPAN重生之路]] |medium=紀錄片 |publisher={{link-en|Drafthouse Films|Drafthouse Films}}}}</ref>。另一位樂評人增田勇一也說：「他們擁有一致的破壞性，勢不可擋，似乎不知道怎麼約束自己。X當時做的事情，我們從來都沒見識過，他們為一切都設立了榜樣。不僅改變了音樂，還改變了整個文化。他們挑戰保守的日本社會，為國民展示了一種全新的生存方式。其實，他們展開的是一場革命」<ref name="wearexDocumentary"/>。[[接吻樂團|接吻樂團]]貝斯手[[吉恩·西蒙斯|吉恩·西蒙斯]]認為：「如果他們出生在英國或美國，用英語唱歌，也許會是世界上最偉大的樂團」<ref name="wearexDocumentary"/>。[[槍與玫瑰|槍與玫瑰]]吉他手{{link-en|理查·福斯特|Richard Fortus}}對他們的評價是：「不同層級的搖滾巨星，超越了[[滾石樂隊|滾石樂隊]]、[[史密斯飛船|史密斯飛船]]或槍與玫瑰」<ref name="wearexDocumentary"/>。

樂團非常受到青少年中的叛逆族群歡迎，如《[[亞洲周刊|亞洲周刊]]》所說「他們受到X JAPAN的特立獨行吸引，並且對X JAPAN非常尊敬」<ref name="asiaweek_death">{{cite web| language = en| last = Seno| first = Alexandra A.| author2 = Murakami, Mutsuko| title = Isolated in Their Grief| work = [[亞洲周刊|亞洲周刊]]| url = http://www.asiaweek.com/asiaweek/98/0522/feat1.html| accessdate = 2013-04-20| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20060214190414/http://www.asiaweek.com/asiaweek/98/0522/feat1.html| archivedate = 2006-02-14| dead-url = no}}</ref>。該周刊描述X JAPAN的音樂是「憤怒的聲音，拒絕服從日本的社會體制」<ref name="asiaweek_death"/>。1998年，廣播電台及電視節目主持人{{link-ja|布萊恩·路易斯|Bryan Burton-Lewis}}說：「在日本，許多孩子正值叛逆期，而他們聽了X JAPAN之後，成為死忠樂迷，不僅穿得像他們一樣，還把樂團視為如空氣般重要的生存必需品」<ref name="asiaweek_death"/>。在音樂紀錄片《{{link-en|全球金屬|Global Metal}}》中，YOSHIKI表示：「一開始，音樂圈、唱片公司和媒體全都討厭我們，我們就像害群之馬，沒人要採訪我們。但我們後來專輯銷量達到兩千萬張，所以，他們最後還是服氣了」<ref name="GlobalMetal"/>。

X JAPAN是日本第一支打進美國市場的搖滾樂團<ref name="rock7356925"/>。截至2016年，樂團共發行五張錄音室專輯，其中連續三張在[[Oricon公信榜|公信榜]]奪下第一名。2007年，《[[滾石_(雜誌)|滾石雜誌]]》將他們的出道專輯《[[BLUE_BLOOD|BLUE BLOOD]]》列為日本史上百大搖滾專輯第15名<ref name="Rolling Stone Japan"/>。據該雜誌報導，樂團已售出超過三千萬張唱片<ref>{{cite news| language = en| title = X Japan's Incredible Ride: Meet Rock's Most Flamboyant Survivors| url = http://www.rollingstone.com/music/features/x-japans-incredible-ride-meet-rocks-most-flamboyant-survivors-20141010| work = [[滾石_(雜誌)|滾石 (雜誌)]]| date = 2010-10-10| accessdate = 2015-04-18| archive-date = 2015-04-22| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150422024314/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/features/x-japans-incredible-ride-meet-rocks-most-flamboyant-survivors-20141010| dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name="ChiSunTimes">{{cite news |language=en |title=X Japan: They're huge (really), and they're (finally) coming to the U.S. |url=http://blogs.suntimes.com/music/2010/08/x_japan_theyre_huge_really_and.html |work=[[芝加哥太陽報|芝加哥太陽報]] |date=2010-08-01 |accessdate=2013-05-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130524154907/http://blogs.suntimes.com/music/2010/08/x_japan_theyre_huge_really_and.html |archivedate=2013-05-24 }}</ref>。此外，他們只憑在[[東京巨蛋|東京巨蛋]]賣出的門票，就累積了一百萬張<ref>{{cite web|language=en|url=http://loudwire.com/x-japan-the-visual-japan-summit-2016-recap-photo-gallery/|title=A Journey With X Japan at the Visual Japan Summit 2016 Recap and Photo Gallery|publisher=Loudwire|date=2016-10-25|accessdate=2017-02-25|archive-date=2017-02-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170201224121/http://loudwire.com/x-japan-the-visual-japan-summit-2016-recap-photo-gallery/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

